				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">What I think the original poster wants to know (and what I'd like to know as well) isn't just what drops there, but what drops that gives mages specifically the biggest bang for the raid points.
<br />

<br />
For instance, in Time there is a mage only Malosinia mask and the Time level pet focus that is a range item so those are two slots that if I do buy upgrades for, I'm not going to spend much on them because I'm planning to replace them.
<br />

<br />
Also, here's another post along the same lines with info <a href="http://forum.magecompendium.com/viewtopic.php?t=13567&highlight=elemental" target="_blank" class="postlink">http://forum.magecompendium.com/viewtopic.php?t=13567&highlight=elemental</a>
<br />

<br />
For me in particular, I have a couple of weak slots (belt and bracer in particular) that I really need to replace, but am not sure exactly what to replace them with.  There are also focus effects I need such as preservation especially nukes, and damage (see bracer), but I'm not sure the best slots to get them on.  Plus, looking at drops on a site doesn't really tell about their rarity and therefore how many points they're going to  cost.
<br />

<br />
Any suggestions you guys could give would be very much appreciated.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
