				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">almost does not matter as far as the xegony ring goes.  if guilds were smart and planned proactively, they would know that the elemental arms for clerics, druids, and shaman (iirc) all have marr's gift effect as does the xegony ring.  and considering 97% of potime players have full elemental armor (save for legs/chest), then your healers are gonna have the effect.
<br />

<br />
since this is the only item, outside of pottery made totem, that magicians can use to help their heal power, then i never understood why it went to healing classes first.  then again, as the above poster mentioned, you can now do the vp quest and get the different version ring.  which i am working on atm...
<br />

